verbose_text: Madsen et al found U shaped association between HDL-C level and all-cause mortality and concluded that extremely high HDL-C paradoxically increases all-cause mortality.19 Hirata et al also demonstrated association of extremely high HDL-C with increased atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease (including CAD and stroke) mortality.20 Although there is no clear explanation for the association of extremely high HDL-C and cardiovascular mortality, investigators suggested a possible genetic variant such as cholesterylester transfer protein (CETP) gene mutation.
